Interface DataSource

All Known Implementing Classes:

public interface DataSource

Converts a document to some representation suitable for input to machine learning algorithms.

Method Detail

initialize

void initialize(Model model,
                ClassifierDef csd)
Initializes this DataSource using a given extraction model, for the given classifier. This prepares a list of features which will be populated for all samples that emerge from this DataSource.

getName

java.lang.String getName()
Returns the name that identifies this data source. This can be e.g. combination of the DataSource type and current document name.

setModel

void setModel(Model model,
              ClassifierDef csd)
Prepares the features defined by the extraction model for use by classifier. Sets options of this data source based on classifier definition, e.g. filters classes or features to be used.

setDocument

void setDocument(Document doc)
Prepares the document so that it can be used as a set of examples to be classified.

setConfidenceThreshold

Sets the minimal confidence a classifier must return for a classified example to be taken into account by the extraction process.

supportsWeightedSamples

Whether this document representation supports SampleSets containing weighted samples.

commitClasses

void commitClasses()
Finalize class information that was set for Samples of this DataSource using SampleIterator. This propagates the class information to the underlying Document.
